snippet.textDisplay: The melding of different musical & cultural elements can be refreshing, unique, & original in our musical landscape. But virtually lifting, almost note for note, the melody, instrumental arrangement, & general texture for two measures (a lifetime in musical terms) is utterly unacceptable, disappointing, & considering Coke Studios & Nestcafe Basement are presently the only two outlets & means of exposure for Pakistani musicians - DISGRACEFUL. Please get your act together,  ASAP, wether this chicanery was under the direction of The Strings or Shani Arshad - ensure this kind obvious plagiarism is not repeated. If this was broadcast in a market that took copyright seriously - Coke Studios would be hearing from the legal representation of The Corrs.

What a nice salad full of melodic and carefully crafted arrangements...
Buleeh Sha´s poems and pakistan sounds full of western rock spices ...( David Guilmour/Carlos Santana guitar references) latin american percussion( Cajón), english keyboards, swiss mikes, tchecoslovakian violinos...celtic flutes. 
Music knows no barriers, only man´s dualistic mind.
Some may claim this season 9 is too much ecletic and lost the point...other may applause  for the new pointed directions.
Fusion?
